column109: The most challenging part of this task is balancing the many factors that impact blood sugar levels, such as protein, carbs, fiber, and portion sizes. Sometime these things aren't clear from the pictures. There could also be ingredients that aren't visible or preparation methods.  Metabolic responses are different for everyone, which will affect a meal's suitability. Comparing meals that aren't very similar is a challenge. Taking into account short-term versus long-term impacts adds another level of difficulty.
column110: I checked if they were valid questions based on the info I was given at the beginning and then evaluated what my answer would be, and if that affected my choice.

column103: I used the questions presented by AI to determine if I had made the correct choice. For example, when AI would question the simple carbohydrates contained within pizza, it reminded me that those types of carbs easily spike glucose levels in individuals with Type II Diabetes. In addition, when it mentioned fiber content, or healthy fats, I knew I had made the correct meal choice, as those are elements that a Type II Diabetic should have in their meals.
column109: On a couple of the photos, I was unable to determine what the food item was. This made it slightly difficult to identify if it was a source of fat, protein, or carbohydrates.
